Sad Boy Radio XCIX: Everything Happens For A Reason? 

Miami DJ, @peexweezy , slides to Chicago to discuss her 10 year career & the events that have shaped her into the woman she is today. PEEWEE has played at @coachella , @rollingloud , and even Paris; however, it's the things that happened behind the scenes that have had the biggest impact. 

PEEWEE has faced countless hardships throughout life that made her question, "why was I put in these positions?" It wasn't until recently where she's started to find the silver lining & own her experiences to help others.  From finding a new identity due to a career ending injury, to being placed in rooms with people with bad intentions. PEEWEE is a survivor of both mental & physical struggles. 

Also discussed, faith in God, most toxic relationship story, @girlsmakebeats , & importance of mental wellness.

UH HUH HONEY 🍯  I’ve been soaking this all in for the past 24hrs but here’s a HUGE THANK YOU to everyone who came out to support me and my crazy ideas! To everyone who helped me bring this to life, my team, my family, my friends….. @fontainebleau !!!!! I’m so outrageously grateful! This is truly just the beginning. I’ll be floading y’all with Honey content but this one is my THANK YOU!! Stay tuned because Honey will activate in a city near you!!! Glory be to God!!!!!!! 🍯✨🍯✨🍯
Still on a high from Saturday! Big s/o to @bluefasebabyy @adrienbroner and @princehasspoken for coming through and partying with us at @thehoneyparty 🍯🍯🍯🍯🍯🍯🍯✨✨✨✨✨✨

STORY TIME!!! I started DJing in college (go NOLES ❤️💛) and after moving back home to Miami I was pressured to find a job and get on my feet post grad. I’m a hustler, so at one point I had 3 jobs at once. Bartending at 2 spots and working at @coast2coastliveshowcase . In this time I was grinding so hard but constantly feeling depressed with a void in my heart because I wasn’t going after what I loved (DJing). So fast forward I remember praying to God asking him to lead me where I’m supposed to if he wanted me to pursue DJing.. and sure enough through bartending I met @dion13miami the man with the plan at Bird Bowl. We chopped it up over a few of my infamous Margaritas and I told him I was an aspiring DJ. He just so happen to be looking for a DJ Thursday nights and offered me to try out. I was sooooo nervous omg I couldn’t even sleep before that gig. Thanks to my brother @zaydaytv_ he got my ass through and we were offered Thursdays at the Birddd! As crazy as it sounded at the time, I told everyone that Bird Bowl was the beginning of something great… and I’d be rocking the big clubs in South beach and around the world. It took some time but I knew God guided me in the right direction… we’re here now! 🦋🦋🦋🦋

I’m forever grateful for @birdbowlmiami @dion13miami & @zaydaytv_ for believing in me and giving me the push start to my dreams! I would literally be nothing without y’all. There’s been so many beautiful and influential people in my path but y’all are the foundation of all things “Peewee”. 

Here’s your sign to stop day dreaming and start chasing your dreams. #DOWHATYOULOVE ‼️

From getting a phone call to DJ in Lagos for one day to spending an entire month throughout the continent is something I’ve never pictured in my wildest dreams. I’m divinely guided and allowing God to take the wheel!

Take that trip! Talk to that guy/girl! Quit your job and go after your dream. Move out your parents and get that place! Walk into that gym you’re intimidated by! Lean into your fears!! There’s such greatness on the other side If your soul is craving it, it’s The God in you guiding your light. 🌍🦋✨
